A bag containing heroin with a street value of Â£1.7m has been discovered unexpectedly by police after a car was pulled over.
Officers stopped the vehicle close to the Black Cat Roundabout, on the A1 near St Neots, on Friday morning. 
Cambridgeshire Police said: "Well that's not what you usually find in a holdall."
A man, in his 30s, has been arrested in connection with class A drug supply and is in police custody.
